comments.body:
Might it make sense to have this as `UFuncError(Exception)` and then inherit from `TypeError` in the cases below? That would leave us free to also use this class for errors that need to inherit from `ValueError` later.

Though, thinking again, perhaps that is just as easily done by later doing:
```
class UFuncError(Exception):
    <what you have now>

class UFuncTypeError(UFuncError, TypeError):
    pass

class UFuncValueError(UFuncError, ValueError):
    pass
```

